Text: We were Domans before the imperials drafted us into their armies. But with our families dead and gone, the Confederacy is to be our home now. Compared to the hell the Empire put us through, though, this is a kami-blessed paradise.
When the time comes, I will send for you,  . Be ready for whatever lies ahead.
Soroban, was it? He surpassed all expectations...to your temporary dismay, perhaps, but to our ultimate benefit, I should think.
Though, regardless of what Genbu may have told you, if you had failed to subdue him, I would have intervened. The wards would have held long enough, I am sure.
<huff> <puff> I'm...I'm not going anywhere. I promise...
Wouldn't do for a guardian stuck on a mountaintop to lose his touch, am I right? So every now and then I'd come down to visit Byakko and goad him into a sparring match.
I tell you, they're not called the Four Lords for nothing. Even when I gave it my best shot, he won. Easily. And you know what makes it worse? I know he was going easy on me!
Back to the Prima Vista so soon?
This spot the Mol have lent us has a beautiful view. Quite spectacular! One time I almost blinded myself staring at the sunset, but it was worth it!
Once we prepare a new gift for the Big One, we can eat the old offering. Yes, yes. I have already consumed several dozen fish, and only a few came back up!

Wasshoi! Though I am often too busy to carry the mikoshi, I make sure to practice so I will not forget how to be most loud and boisterous. Gyofun dropped a book on my head yesterday to silence me, but I persevere!
I got ever so slightly, just the tiniest bit carried away and built a full archery range in the open area behind the main pavilion. I am sure you will love it, yes, yes!

All sorts of people have come to see our Namazu effigy! Their openmouthed gaping can only mean that they are in awe of its majesty. Yes, yes. It is just a matter of time until tales of its glory reach foreign lands.
Now that we have made our festival a success, we need only continue at this pace for the next seven years! I have not slept since we arrived here, and I will not start now. No, no.
I am happy to sew festival attire for each and every one of our participating Namazu. Yes, yes. Seven down, seven hundred and seventy to go!
The whole world seems brighter with our altar all aglow. Yes, yes. I wonder if our ancestors felt this way, too.
Between carrying the mikoshi and shouting, crafting and shouting, and his usual routine of getting injured and shouting, I worry that Gyoshin has been taking very little time to rest.
I suppose it was too much to hope that Gyoshin's carelessness would be cured so easily. Yes, yes. If he were just a bit more astute, he might realize I─ Never mind. Forget I said anything.

I hesitate to mention this, as I am afraid the other two might start trying to sacrifice each other again, but making the dolls to burn is no easy task. They require all sorts of materials. Yes, yes. Aaall sorts.
As careless as he is, Gyoshin cuts quite a striking figure when he sets his mind to something. Yes, yes...

Welcome, welcome! I have been assigned this prominent counter space for one reason─to provide material rewards to our loyal volunteers. The more people who come to lend a fin, the more items we can offer!
Great news,  ! We have gone from offering many items to offering many, many items! I recommend our new authentic Namazu effigy─live sacrifice not included, no, no.
You can finally purchase a mikoshi of your very own─are you not delighted? Now the melodious squeaking of Namazu steps and a chorus of cheerful “wasshois” will accompany you wherever you go. Forever!
You want to try your hand at being a mikoshi bearer? I am afraid we built the poles at Namazu height and for Namazu fins. You, my friend, are more suited to being the one carried! Yes, yes.
There is a trick to bearing the weight of a mikoshi comfortably. It takes time and practice, and Namazu who lack discipline do not remain bearers for long. It has become something of a problem...

We might have become ever so slightly carried away with our plans for mikoshi mass production... On a completely unrelated note, we have decided to reward our invaluable festival assistants with their very own mikoshi!
You need only give a shout, and your bearers will come waddling! Go forth, and share the wondrous spectacle of our mikoshi with people near and far!
Is it true!? Did Alphinaud really board a vessel bound for the imperial capital!? Well, if anyone can negotiate a peace with the Empire, it will be our young diplomat!

We gathered what scraps of intelligence we could─meself from within Eorzea, an' Alphinaud from his Far Eastern sources─but there's a limit to what a bloke can learn about the Empire from outside its borders.
Still, I'd never think to invite meself aboard an imperial bloody airship! 'Twas impulsive. Reckless. Ye've got to admire the lad's style!
'Twould seem Master Alphinaud has placed himself squarely in the path of danger. As a fellow Scion, I shall render whatever aid I can to ensure his safe return.
Though he is but half the size of my courageous brother, 'twould seem Alphinaud's bravery looms twice as large. Even Hoary might hesitate before embarking alone into the heart of the Empire!

It is my sacred duty to stand guard over the altar. Yes, yes. You never know when someone will get hungry and try to purloin an offering for a snack. That is why I keep my eyes wide open day and night.

But I do understand how they feel, yes, yes. Those ripe vegetables, those succulent fish... And with guarding being such hungry work and all... Sometimes the food is halfway to my mouth before I realize what is happening!
Now that the Xaela come to visit our festival, my time on duty─which is all the time, yes, yes─is much improved. The festival is more lively now...and they often bring gifts! Edible gifts.

I love how these Xaela festival activities give me the chance to experience new things! Yes, yes. Back at Yuzuka Manor I only sorted jars, but look at me now! Sorting targets, sorting ropes, sorting thicker ropes...
Quite a few of our many, many attendees have come bearing gifts. Sorting through them all is hard on the fins, but fascinating. I can even taste the ones I think are food! I am sometimes wrong.
What a realistic depiction! As I stand here, gazing into his eyes, I can almost feel his pain as he succumbs to the dizzying heat. And yet, he smiles. I think I...understand him. Yes, yes...

Do you ever think about what it would be like to be one of those dolls─to know that your fate is to die in agony as you are consumed by flames, yet be unable to scream? No? I cannot be the only one...
The moment I saw the archery demonstration, I knew I must take up the bow! That is why I volunteered to run the range here. Soon, I too shall stand with tranquil power, and shoot with fluid grace!
<sigh> I still cannot get the hang of it. Who knew archery would be so difficult with fins... Wait, you knew? You knew and didn't tell me!?
Would you care to ride this noble yol to Dhoro Iloh above?
Would you care to ride this noble yol to Nhaama's Retreat below?
Greetings! If you love the Moonfire Faire as much as I do, you should go and see the main attraction in Costa del Sol!
Glad you could join us! If you need anything related to the Moonfire Faire, from information to fireworks, you can find it all here!
So, what do you think of the Eorzean Nimble Warrior course? It's not going to be there forever, so enjoy it while you can!
Of all the challengers to complete the course, you're one of the most popular with the crowd. Why not give it another try?
Now that's the way to do it! The other Nimble Warriors can learn a lot from watching you.
You know, if you register first and complete all three sections in order, you'll receive a prize!
I think Haermaga will want to see you. He likes to personally congratulate every competitor that completes the course! Not that there are many of those, unfortunately...
If you fancy running the course again, be sure to speak with Beaudefoin first. I can only give prizes to registered competitors, so don't forget!
Welcome to the festive phenomenon that is Valentione's Day! Pray join Lisette and her emissaries in this celebration of love, pure and passionate!
How goes your exploration of the tower? I expect that running around slaying fiends is second nature to you, but be sure to keep your wits about you.

After I became the leader of the Confederacy and defeated Hiruko, I went back into the tower for a second helping, so to speak. I thought I would be able to reach the top, but I could climb no higher than the fiftieth floor.

It was then that I realized how our founder must have felt all those years ago. A dead leader is no use to anyone, so like him, I withdrew. Though it still galls me to this day, I know I made the right choice.

Have you heard? The Immortal Flames will be conducting massive military maneuvers as part of the Rising's remembrances. And you can bet your bottom britches that this Mythril Eye reporter will be there to summarize the story for our respected readers!

Full many did we lose to the fires of the Calamity. During this period of remembrance, let us pay tribute to those who are no longer with us, that their memory might shine the way to a brighter future.
Have you heard? They say there's trouble at the Gold Saucer! As a matter of fact, there's a woman on Emerald Avenue who came back from there not long ago. Claims something awful happened to her.
If you're thinking of heading to the Gold Saucer for the festival, I'd think twice if I were you. Word has it something strange is going on there.
I was hoping to attend the festival at the Gold Saucer. That is, until I heard the rumors. Anyone who steps foot in there is either brave, or an incredible fool.
If you've a mind to pore over these tomes, perhaps you should go and speak with Guiding Star in Revenant's Toll first.
'Tis still somewhat strange to speak with you here, in a place I once thought neither of us would find ourselves. Not that your presence is unwelcome, of course!

By the way─I told the children that you sometimes visit the enclave, and that they should pay their respects, but they seem to be very busy with their guild. I expect they will seek you out in due time...which is to say, when they want to involve you in one of their adventures.
You look well,  ! Hale and healthy as ever. I am perhaps a touch less so, though I did manage to survive the long journey across the seas not once, but twice now!
Since my return, I have taken to sharing my experiences with any who would hear them. In this way, I can broaden the horizons of those around me─or so I like to believe. Isildaure would surely agree!
, is that you? I certainly did not expect to see you this evetodaytodaythis eve!

As you may have guessed, when I am not on patrol, I put my culinary talents to use here in the stalls. I hope to share with the others F'lhaminn's wisdom, and see what other original dishes we can create!
Good eveningmorrowdayevening to you,  ! Our dearest friend who helped us to return to Doma!
It should come as no surprise that the mood during our voyage home was rather unlike our first across the seas. Singing, dancing─you would have enjoyed it very much!

I'm terribly sorry, madamsir, but until we have discovered the source of the disturbances here at the Gold Saucer, and dealt with it accordingly, we are not permitted to sell any festival merchandise.
As part of the celebration, the Gold Saucer has made a number of extravagant items available for purchase with MGP. But you must act quickly, for they will only be available for a limited time.
Lasting change must be built upon a stable foundation. The Ten Thousand Stalls are a good start, but we should strive to do more to see our people fed.
Progress and pleasure go hand in hand. Which is to say that, for all we have accomplished in improving the lot of our people, we must never forget to enjoy the benefits for ourselves.
...And no, this is not simply an excuse to justify my love of Triple Triad. It is one of many excuses, I will have you know.
...Hmm? Did you hear that? No? Must've been my imagination, then. Carry on!
What fools, these Xaela! Thinking no one would notice their clumsy attempts to sneak inside the Kienkan!
Little do they know how lucky they are to have been caught by me and not Hakuro─he would have cut them all down without a second thought!
Not bad, eh? Hard to imagine that there was once a pile of rubble where I stand, is it not? At this rate, we'll have the whole of the enclave cleaned up in no time!
Good to see everyone taking up their old trades, like these ones here. It may well be time for me to follow suit...
...What was my old trade, you ask? Heh, what do you think it was?

Whatever happens out there, I have to believe everything will be all right here. So long as someone─be it me or another─remains to watch over these children. Especially those who have no one else left...
I'll never forget what that woman did to us. But as long as Azami is happy, that's all that matters.
She seemed so sad. All she wanted was a persimmon...

You really did Idyllshire a favor by clearin' out the Arboretum. Thanks to you, Edgyth was able to uncover all sorts of Sharlayan secrets. Hopefully, it'll lead to better produce bein' grown around these parts.
As a mage, I have some few scholarly acquaintances of my own, and will reach out to them for their insights. It may not be much, but 'tis my own little way of aiding Mistress Alisaie.
We Scions who can still perform our duty must take up the burden of our comrades who cannot. We will continue our watch over the beast tribes and do whatever else may be required of us.
Riol has left to rendezvous with Alliance forces. He means to serve in Thancred's stead in their infiltration missions.
Ocher, Sister, and I will take turns to keep watch over the slumbering Archons. We'll not leave them untended even for a moment.
Confound these old bones... Useless as I am, I should have been the one to be struck down...
It cannot be discounted that Mistress Krile has heard the voice as well. I will ask Tataru to send her word of what has come to pass.
When the call comes from the Mol, the Sun will rise to stand with you as we did in Doma.
No man can behold the Buduga in battle and fail to be moved by our courage. If we can but capture Hien's imagination with our valor, the rest of him will surely follow...
The Dotharl are ready to fight. We always are.
Strange... Amidst the radiance of your being, I sense a shadow. I pray it is but my imagination.

In a place such as the Steppe, where myriad tribes exist side by side, it is important to respect each other's ways. And it would be wise indeed to respect the beliefs of those who would gladly render up body and soul to the Dusk Mother.
I have heard the tidings. To think that Y'shtola and Urianger should be struck down as well... If the Ascians are indeed the culprits, what exactly is their goal?
Many of our neighbors have sent emissaries to treat with Lord Hien. I dare to hope that our alliance will grow into a formidable force.
I am minded to dispatch more shinobi to the provinces. We cannot have too many eyes searching for Master Alphinaud nor too many lips whispering the rumors pertaining to Zenos.
First Thancred, and now Y'shtola and Urianger... I'll consult the scholarly types around here, but I really wish I could do more. Keep looking after Alisaie and everyone else, all right?

There's a lot on Alisaie's mind at the moment, but she's as determined as ever. I could see it in her eyes when she came to discuss the Ironworks. It inspires me to redouble my efforts here in Kugane!
Greetings, my friend. If you are looking for Tataru, she has left with Mistress Alisaie to speak with the good people of Garlond Ironworks.

I'm reliably informed that Doma seeks to forge an alliance... The thing about alliances, of course, is that they can be so very expensive. While I daresay it's within the company's means to provide the necessary funds, it is for the chairman to decide whether such an investment would be worth the risk.

As Antecedent, Minfilia fostered connections with numerous scholars and research organizations. There's the professors Erik and Lamberteint, the scholars of the Sons of Saint Coinach, the myriad guilds of Eorzea, the Council...and the list goes on.

Owing to her foresight, we have many allies to which we might turn in this dark hour. Minfilia might not have stood upon the front lines like some of us, but without her work the Scions could not have functioned half as well. There's a lot I can learn from her.
On the matter of Nhaama's power and the alliance, the gods have remained silent. That is their way of telling us to choose with our hearts.
Though the Mol have no love for war, we love our home fiercely. Should the Steppe be threatened, we will rise up to protect it─as will full many other tribes, I believe.
The council has resumed, and the leaders offer their assurances that they have the remaining agenda well in hand. They bid you godsspeed in shedding light on the mystery.
The most important thing when building a playground is to make it safe. No sharp corners for the children to bash their heads on!
The entrance is rather grand, wouldn't you say? The little embellishments were my idea.
Not wanting the steel from the imperial tower to go to waste, we took it to Tsuranuki. He was practically jumping for joy!
Of course, I could not disappoint Master Ishibushi after he put me in charge of constructing the pavilion. It is coming along rather nicely, if I do say so myself.
If you ask me, I have more cause to be upset. With him in such a state, any visitors are sure to assume he is Genbu, not I!
Have I truly become host to a great kami? What if it does not wish to leave?

It took me centuries to come to terms with Tenzen's passing. That Suzaku had not came as no surprise. Like us, Seiryu cared for him deeply, and I cannot help but worry that he too may struggle to accept your part in this...
Oh, my beloved, I pray you yet watch over me...
I know she says she isn't, but boy does she look like the Firebird of legend! I bet she gave you the fight of your life, too! I might have to ask for a sparring match...
Are you sure you have not crossed paths with Tamamo Gozen? No? And you would tell me if you had? Ah, yes, of course. Why would you not...?
Seeing as we're already nearby on Scion business, we volunteered for the security detail at the council meeting. None of us could have foreseen what unfolded there...
It pains me to see the young ones suffer so. While 'tis true that we are hardened by adversity, such a weight is heavier than anyone has any right to bear.

Wherever he is at the moment, I'm sure Alphinaud is doing the best he can. That's all that any of us can do, and I mean to do just that. We'll continue keeping an eye on primals, don't you worry, and tend to them as well if needs be.
I've taken excerpts from the chief's report on Omega and loaded them onto the terminal there. Feel free to take a look.
I would've liked to add Nero's observations as well, but that man is nowhere to be found. Did you know he sold Rowena the pattern for a new uniform!?
Oh, and speaking of nowhere to be found, I wonder how far Alpha has gone. Not outside of Eorzea, surely... You haven't spotted our little chick on your travels have you?

When the Ala Mhigans left to return to their homeland, we felt as though we were the ones left behind. But things are starting to look brighter for us as well. After all these years, to think that there's still honest work for honest pay... I'll earn the coin to get back into the city yet!

The other day, a man from the East Aldenard Trading Company paid us a visit. He said that they needed hands for the rebuilding effort in Gyr Abania. That they were looking to hire folk among the poor and the displaced.

Long have I cursed my lot and the powers that be. I thought that I would die with a curse on my lips. To suddenly be given another chance... Can this be true? Can there really be a better life for us?
Me? I'm recruiting workers to help bring Gyr Abanian salt to Ul'dah. It's a business venture that aims to help both refugees and Ul'dah's own poor to begin anew.
Perhaps if I remain here, she will return. Yes, yes. Surely that would be the best course of action...
I tell you, I've got a bad feeling about this...
Some folks crave excitement, but if you ask me, nothing beats peace and quiet.
There are few in whom I would place my faith without question. I count the Four Lords among these. They will not fail.
I had made peace with death before Koryu returned. This, I believed...until he stood there before us all, and the long life I had lived felt not at all satisfying...
I don't know why everyone's so worried. I mean, we've got the whole gang back together, right? The Four Lords! What could possibly go wrong?

Doesn't speak too highly of the rest of us that we could only hang back and watch while the Four Lords did all the hard work. But hey─we've got a few more millennia till we have to do this again, right? Time enough for me to train that I can do my bit when the time comes!
So it has come to this...
You may think it a dull, thankless task to stand watch over the sacred crystal for several thousand years. Frankly...you would not be entirely wrong to say so. Nevertheless, it is our duty.
First he was consumed by his raging aramitama, and now he's become an even bigger turtle! And I thought I led a charmed life.
I'll do my best to live up to Genbu's name. That said, it would be nice if you came by every so often to cheer me on...
Whatever is the matter,  ? Could it be that a tiger...has your tongue?
Ohoho! Do not pretend you are not amused. Genbu taught me that one.
If only Koryu were the sole source of tragedy in this world of ours. But we know better, do we not?
Though it perhaps is not on such a grand scale, our work continues, for it falls to the Four Lords to safeguard this realm.
I overheard some of the younger auspices whispering how odd it was that “Seiryu” is a giant snake. Some rubbish about ancient Hingan etymology.

My name is my name─that's what I have to say on the matter. If my appearance is somehow at odds with your expectations, then that is the fault of you and whatever wild fantasies articulated by wandering minstrels you have elected to believe.
Master Gosetsu will not return to find us soft and sagging, oh no! Constant training and iron discipline for these warriors!
With the return of our brothers and sisters, the repair of the enclave proceeds with ever greater momentum! Soon our eyes must fall upon Monzen, and the bitter task of dismantling my poor children...

It would seem that peace with the Empire was not so simple after all...
Be that as it may, I take great joy in the return of our countrymen─the reunion of family means more to Doma's restoration than any amount of supplies.
I was not surprised to hear the Empire played us foul at the prisoner exchange, but at least our people were able to escape. It is good to see new faces here at the House.
! Thank the kami for you and Lord Hien. Our people have come home, and Doma rejoices!
Don't you worry,  ! Inspector Hildibrand will be back in a jiffy!
All this time, the Ame-no-Murakumo was in the Red's treasure vault. And there I thought it was no more than a story...
Triple Triad? If you promise to leave I shall humor you this once, but let us be brief.
I have no time for games. Unless you have business with the magistrate, I suggest you be on your way.
If you would feel shame, let it be for distracting an officer from his duties, not defeat in some childish game.
Well, what did you expect? I am a guard, not a Triple Triad duelist. Now please, be on your way.
A draw... I suppose this means you wish to take up more of my time?
Triple Triad? Yes, I am familiar. For better or worse, I was often in the company of Garlean officers who enjoyed the game. If you wish to play, you need only ask.
Yes, I am familiar with Triple Triad. For better or worse, I was often in the company of Garlean officers who enjoyed the game. But I'd rather not dwell on such dark times.
It seems I learned more from the Garlean officers than I'd care to admit...
Impressive. It would seem the Garleans have more to fear than your prowess in combat.
Well played, my friend. Would you care to play again? I'd rather not end things on a draw.
A game of Triple Triad? I was hoping you might ask. At last, an opportunity to test my stratagems.
My apologies, misssir, but might I have a moment longer to think? Devising a winning stratagem for my cards is proving more troublesome than I thought.
I won? I won! Oh, that was absolutely splendid. If you care to play again, I would be more than happy to oblige.
Oh dear. It would seem my stratagems are not quite enough to compete with a true Triple Triad duelist. You have given me much to think on.
That I could hold my own against an experienced duelist is more than I could have hoped for, but are you satisfied with only a draw?

It is fortunate that we spent so much time smashing mikoshi into one another during the festival─our charge was most vigorous, yes, yes? Though our ornamental Big One is looking a bit worse for the wear. Quite...squished.
I can scarcely believe how much the festival preparations fell behind in my absence! Thank goodness both of my fins are intact. To work, to work!
I hope to visit the Far East again sometime. I'm sure there are many more fortifications to sssee! Not to mention more hot springs─frankly, I think J'olhmyn could use another chance to relax.
Everything turned out alright this time, but I can't afford to let my guard down again. That's why my new training regimen focuses on readying every muscle in my body to spring at any moment.
How can I hope to protect the M tribe if I can't even best someone like Nhaza'a?
No! Get a hold of yourself, M'zhet! You are the brave and handsome future nunh! You will become stronger, and you will follow in your father's footsteps!
The bonds of friendship I have forged with the Velodyna Gatekeepers and Namazu prove that Tsukumo continues to guide me. As do you.
You have my personal thanks for rescuing Alpa, of course. It wouldn't do to have visitors to Kugane go missing, especially ones that are ostensibly my responsibility!
Thanks to the efforts of Lord Hien and his allies, my brothers and I are finally free from the Garleans. It feels a dream even now.
Tell me, have you heard of Triple Triad? It is a most wondrous game. The researchers here at the pier have been teaching me how to play.
It seemed simple enough at first, but it is actually quite complex. Why, I could spend all day sitting here thinking of stratagems. In fact, I often do just that.
Curses! We can't leave this devilry uninvestigated, but if I leave my post, no one will be keeping an eye on the Impresario. If only an obviously skilled adventurer would pass by...
In order to undertake the quest “The Sinister Soirée,” you must first complete the quest “It's Probably Pirates.”
Have you gained access to the masquerade yet? I hear tell that the Continental Circus has quite outdone itself with the décor this year. No doubt in order to lure in more innocent victims!
Never fear, I will continue to monitor the Impresario's activities without rest! You are free to keep an eye on the happenings within the manor.
What a peculiar costume! Absolutely perfect for our marvelous masq─ Oh, that's your real face, is it? Well then, carry on.
As long as there are nights, there will be devilry. Mark my words... Er, mark them down as another outstanding idea for a slogan, I mean!
Come one, come all, to the marvelous masquerade!
Ah, another vict─ahem, visitor! Are you ready to revel?
This is the greatest day of my life! It's also the only day so far!
Hey, you're back! Are you tempting fate? Can I come?
<sigh> Being alive is all well and good, but this floating and bobbing is exhausting...
I don't mind the company, just...revel quietly, please.
None of the other decorations ever had faith in me to achieve my dreams. But look at me now! I'm a bat!
How do I look? Do you feel like I'm peering into your soul? I mean, I'm not, but don't I look like I could?
To think that I, once a mere ornament, would someday send people into shrieking fits of adoration!
I must say, the thought of singing in front of everybody does make me rather nervous. But then again, they might not be able to hear me above Baenfaeld, anyway.
I think we can all breathe a sigh of relief now that all of our plans have come together. Thankfully, the festival-goers seem to be equally delighted!
As for the choir, I think we know the songs well enough to perform without a conductor, but we would be delighted to have you lead us again!
Have you heard? We've got a choir comin' for a singsong! That'll get everyone into the festive spirit!
Apparently, we'll have some musicians performing for us this year. Not exactly my cup of tea, but I suppose some people might enjoy it.

Oh, you're the conductor, are you? Good luck with that choir─you'll need it. The only one who seems to know what he's doing is that Augustiniel fellow. I'm surprised he's willing to put his reputation on the line by singing with a bunch of complete beginners.
Come one, come all! Welcome to the Starlight Celebration! Prepare yourselves for the greatest show the realm has ever seen!
Do I have the honor of addressing the esteemed conductor of the choir? My heart soars to imagine the spectacle of musical genius that awaits us!

Timber gathered from near the One River is highly resilient to water and humidity, making it incredibly durable. In fact, most of the reconstruction plans rely heavily on these kinds of local resources.
You think I am being lazy, don't you? I would have you know, stepping back to see the bigger picture is an important part of our work.
Even simple structures like this have their challenges.
I have a feeling the ceiling is a bit higher than we need it...
Seems like a lot of effort for a bunch of volunteer guards, but we have our orders.
Watching the construction of the school is a wonderful opportunity for the children to learn of traditional Doman joinery.
So this will be the new headquarters for the Doman Adventurers' Guild? I can hardly wait!
I heard you've been making lots of donations! That's what Miss Minazuki says anyway.
We're not playing, this is serious! I'm making sure the others are training properly.
Miss Minazuki told us to keep away from the builders. It's dangerous, she says.
History's interesting but I like doing sums. There's always a right answer!
I'm looking for creepy-crawlies! Watch out─you'll step on them!
A great big school, just for us! How exciting!
It's funny sitting in a school while it's still being built! Maybe there's something we can do to help?
The grown-ups made this lovely garden for us! We can play here whenever we want!
Miss Minazuki is very clever, you know. Even our Master of Lessons used to do everything she said!
I love school! Can we still come here when we're older?
Sometimes I miss my friends in Eorzea. There aren't many Miqo'te or Lalafells around here, are there?
Where should I go on my first adventure? Maybe I can go to see Mister Boulder!
The enclave would be a great place to play hide-and-seek, don't you think? We should play after school!
I can't wait to be grown-up and go wherever I like! Then I'll travel all around the world!
I want to help Yozan and Koharu when they get in trouble. If I read lots of books, I can give them good advice!
Although Master Ishibushi has taught me so much already, I feel like it will take decades before I even begin to approach his level of competence.
Minazuki has asked me to help look after the children, but they are generally so well behaved there is not much for me to do.
The children cannot spend all of their time studying. It is good for them to get outside and stretch their legs, especially after sitting still for such a long time.
I am often asked to relate tales of our time in Eorzea. Although I wish we could have gone there under happier circumstances, I have a wealth of pleasant memories to share.
Have you happened to see Isildaure on your travels? I do hope he is well. Perhaps one day we can enjoy tea together in this pavilion.
Those children certainly keep me on my toes! Not that they mean to cause mischief, but they are so adventurous that I cannot help but worry.

I cannot describe how much it means for us to return to our homeland and lead meaningful lives. The people of Mor Dhona showed us incredible kindness but I could not escape the feeling that we were a burden to them.
I find myself unsure as to how I can contribute to the enclave. I lack Tsuranuki's skill as a craftsman, nor do I have a gift for the culinary arts like Higiri...
Perhaps the enclave guard will be a chance to make something of myself. I have always fancied becoming a fighter of some sort!
Mitsuba and I have been attempting to recreate Eorzean dishes using local ingredients. While there are a few differences, I would say that we are getting closer to the flavors I enjoyed in Mor Dhona.
Thanks to you, I was able to return to Doma to live with my father.
I still feel enormously grateful for everything the Confederacy did for me. In fact, I am able to put the skills to good use, and I continue to work as a shipwright.
Clearing away the rubble is only the beginning! We plan to fill the area with a host of new buildings to encourage the rebirth of the enclave.
Kozakura and the Shazenkai hold the purse strings around here, it seems. Time will tell if we were right to place our trust in them...
As the nezumi bugyo, it is my solemn duty to ensure that this, the most auspicious year of the rat, is celebrated across national borders.
You have perhaps seen similar efforts by my compatriots in years past, but I assure you─anything they have done, I shall do better!
If you might be persuaded to cleave any more suspiciously sentient mochi in the name of rats, we would welcome the assistance! We yet have our hands and paws full with cutting advent cakes.
Oh, hullo! If you are hoping to peruse our selection of festive wares, I am afraid they are not quite ready!
Hello, my dear. The prizes for this All Saints' Wake's most raucous revelers aren't ready just yet, but you can soak in the haunting atmosphere while you wait!
I do not yet have any traditional Heavensturn souvenirs to offer, but the goods-bearers are scampering here as we speak!
Rumor has it that our wolf went and offered himself up to the Sekiseigumi in a grand, noble gesture to spare Shigure from havin' to bear his guts to the world. Will wonders never cease...

So we was right about that satchel, eh? Mind-befuddlin' stuff what no honest fellow ought to keep close at hand. It's like I tell these folks all the time: whatever “mischief” we may get up to hardly compares to the crimes of the moneyed bastards hobnobbin' with the bugyo and his ilk.
Cor, we did it! We saved Shigure!
Slowly but surely we're rebuilding our fortunes, one day at a time. Before long we'll be buying land and building homes, and then...then they have to accept us, right?
Some people will tell you that all you need to change your stars is a chance. A steady job with a modest salary. These people are fools.

The important thing for us now is not to fall prey to the lie that is the Ul'dahn dream, for that is but a tool they use to divide us. Only through united purpose and collective action will we achieve lasting change for ourselves and our children.
I reckon you saw Pearl Lane for yourself. It's still got a ways to go, but it's a start. Here, too. Call me naive if you like, but I sincerely believe it.
It's not every day you make friends with a secret collective of talking animals, after all! Even if Soroban hadn't decided to remain at Reisen Temple, I wouldn't have wanted to stay away.

I still struggle to believe that Soroban has been chosen for such an important duty. Not that he is undeserving or ill-suited to it! But I knew him when he was very young, and oh, the stories I could tell you...
His grand plan is to bring about more calamities!? This is insanity! This madman must be stopped at all costs!
Now that we have learned the Emperor's true purpose, war has become an inevitability. 'Tis times like these I curse my own uselessness in battle...
The Ascians are terrible beings indeed that they would found an entire nation to further their dark designs. 'Twould seem that the Empire's history is as sinister as Ishgard's own.
The Empire exists to wage war, and war it shall have. But its vast armies pour in like the tides themselves─this could very well be the greatest military threat Eorzea has ever faced...

It makes a twisted kind of sense that the Empire was built by the chaos bringers themselves. The revelation yet rattles me, but now that we know our enemies are one and the same, we have a target upon which to unleash the full force of the Alliance!
We suspected Ascians meddled in the shadows of the Empire, but the truth is far beyond my wildest imagining. At least now we know the face of our enemy, and need not hesitate to strike at its heart!
I refuse the Emperor's words with all of my being. What justice is there in an ideal that demands the sacrifice of so many?
I was born in the Empire, but I will never serve the Emperor. Only the Seedseer commands my loyalty.
I am glad we arrived in time to aid in the battle. Though our vanguard may be small, these few are our chosen elite─the finest warriors of the Far East.
Send me to the front lines, if you please. We'll give the imperials a taste of the Maelstrom's cannons─not to mention my axe!
The Temple Knights have deployed in full strength. Eorzea's future is Ishgard's future, and our fates ride upon the outcome of this conflict.

My first engagement as Flame General, and it is full-scale war with the Empire...
I feel some measure of nervousness, of course, but I swear I will make Father proud in the battles to come!

In case you were wondering, we won't be sailing off to fight in Eorzea in the foreseeable future. Our ships just aren't equipped for that kind of voyage. But you may be sure we'll do our part against the Empire closer to home.
Many tribes have pledged their warriors to the alliance that they might protect the Steppe and our way of life. Perhaps an outside war is what is needed to end the conflict amongst my people.

Garlond Ironworks and the researchers over at Saint Coinach's Find are doing all they can to find that beacon. Until they do, I suggest you get some rest and prepare for whatever it is that cloaked stranger has planned.

Speaking of preparations, have you had time to try on the traveling clothes I prepared for you? The material is light but durable, and colored with the finest dyes Kugane has to offer. Oh, I do hope they fit.
Our brothers and sisters are fallen, 'tis true, but duty will not afford us time to wallow in misery. Until they are returned to us, we must work twice as hard.
I am afraid there is still no change in the Scions' condition, and the means to wake them from their slumber yet eludes us. I pray this beacon at the Crystal Tower might guide us to an answer.
In light of the present condition of the Scions, even Riol has returned from afield. Never has there been a greater need to marshal our resources.
My brother says he will work twice as hard in the Scions' stead, which likely means I must work thrice as hard if I am to match his pace.
I never realized just how critical a role the Archons played in all that we do here. It won't be easy to make up for their absence.
You needn't worry about the Scions. Ocher, my sister, and I have been keeping over them in shifts ever since they arrived at the Rising Stones. If only they would give some sign of stirring...
Everyone labors tirelessly to fulfill the Scions' duties in their absence, and yet I... <sigh> I sometimes wonder what worth yet remains in these old bones of mine.
Grandfather doubts his ability to contribute to the Scions, and try as I might, I cannot assuage his doubts. Would that Homei was here. He would know what to say.
I thought things couldn't get any worse when the Garleans were gearin' up for war. Then word reached me the Scions were in trouble... We need to find that beacon, an' find it quick.
What is it now? I've already spoken to one of your “Scions” about this disappearing aether business.
I consider myself an expert in such matters, but never have I heard of a soul's trail ending without a trace. It's unprecedented. Preposterous!
The greater part of the Temple Knights have been dispatched to hold the Ala Mhigan border. Though only few remain here in Ishgard, I assure you our people yet remain in good hands.
The Confederacy bows to no one...but I see the wisdom in joining Lord Hien's alliance. The Empire threatens us all, and only by banding together can we hope to keep what is ours.
Word of your exploits at lord Hien's side have reached even here. Though it pains me that I cannot join him in battle, our duties here are of no less importance. I pray you, keep him safe.
We can barely find time to rest now that the fighting's started. I had a mind to join in the fighting myself, but Lyse insisted that I see to things here.

! I thought you would be with the others defending the border at Ala Mhigo. I intended to volunteer my services, but alas, my dear brother was a few steps faster. With him gone, it falls to me to keep watch over House Fortemps.

Worry not about Lord Emmanellain. He appeared devastated at the news that he could not venture to Ala Mhigo, that much is true. But deep down, I believe he is quite relieved that he can stay here at the manor.

Don't look like that. Shtola survived being cast adrift in the Lifestream, didn't she? Her soul is nothing if not resilient─and the same goes for all of Louisoix's students. So stop worrying about whether you'll see them again, and focus on what can be done in the here and now.

Is it true!? The other Scions have fallen ill!? Gods...
Please,  , be careful. If we should lose you too, I...I don't know what I would do.
Should I spot a sin eater from afar, I must run to notify my commander at once. A moment's delay can prove the difference between life and death.
I heard of the misfortune which befell young Alphinaud, and it pains me that I have neither the skills nor the knowledge to be of help to him.
I can but do my part to defend Eorzea, and ensure the world is no worse off on the day he finally awakens.

Ah, a welcome sight in these troubled times. Though I suspect it will not be long before you are ushered away on some urgent business. Still, you are more than welcome to rest here for as long as you wish.
! We heard you collapsed on the battlefield, but I see you've made a rather swift recovery.

As for the other Scions, while there is little we can do in helping find a cure to rouse them from sleep, we are making every effort to take up what duties of theirs we can. Namely, the prevention of primal summoning, and slaying any that should be called forth. We all must do our part to keep the realm safe.
Those who can resist the influence of primals are an invaluable asset in our work. Still, I would be lying were I to say I was not initially opposed to fighting alongside the Butcher.

It goes without saying defending the border is paramount, but that's not to say we can neglect the threat of primals. With so much to do, I doubt we'll be returning to the Rising Stones any time soon.
When the time came to stand against the Garleans, we of the Blue did not hesitate to join the fray. After the war is won, perhaps we can engage in trade with the people of Eorzea.
It is said you fell in the battle against the Empire. I understand that duty bids you return to the fray, but please─be careful.

Do you recall the shadow I sensed amidst your radiance? I thought perhaps it was foretelling recent events, but...its presence still lingers. I know not what journeys lie ahead, but I wish you safe travels.
What is this I hear of the khagan being defeated in battle by hands other than mine? I can but imagine the strength of this adversary, but you would do well not to fall a second time.
These Garleans believe they can bring all the world to heel, but the Sun will not abide such tyranny.
I must confess, the offices have not been quite the same since Tataru left... They're considerably quieter, for one thing. But don't tell her I said that, all right?
The Alliance recently sent word that it was you who saved Lord Hien and the others in their confrontation with the Empire. Words fail to express my gratitude for your timely assistance.
Word has it the Empire's already planning another attack. The folk here aren't fit for fighting, but we'll see to it the soldiers don't want for provisions. It's the least we can do to help.
With the Garleans practically knocking at our door again, workers are getting tense. But don't you worry─we'll keep this place safe.
Ah, MistressMaster  , what a pleasure it is to see you. If there is aught you need, pray do not hesitate to ask.
MistressMaster  ! My apologies, misssir. I meant to go and visit you in the infirmary, but... Well, I'm glad to see you up and about!

I can but wonder how fare our brothers and sisters as the battle rages within the Ghimlyt Dark. I have faith my comrades will prevail in the end, but should the worst come to the worst, those who yet remain here must be ready to defend the Twelveswood.

It feels as though I returned from the Ghimlyt Dark but a few bells ago, and already there is talk of redeployment. Harrowing though the battle was, I must confess I am somewhat eager to return and do my part.

The battle with the Empire wages on, and every soldier we can spare has been sent to the front line. Even I, for my part, have done battle in the Ghimlyt Dark. Having forced back their vanguard, we afforded ourselves time to recuperate.

You must be the one Leofard keeps talkin' about. He sent me here to pick up a few things, but I thought I'd stick around and take in the sights. These goblins make some interestin' machines, you know!
What a wonderful nightmorningdaynight for gathering herbs! Do you know, I found some lovely little cards with pictures and some numbers on them. I wonder if they are used for some sort of game?
Now that the whole episode with the interdimensional rift has come to an end, life has returned to a state of relative normality. Perhaps I should take up a hobby to occupy my spare time...
An old friend of mine has become obsessed with a card game from the West. At first I scoffed at her new pastime, but the more I watched her play, the more the game intrigued me.
I even went so far as to trade with some foreign explorers and build a respectable deck myself. There are so many rules to learn...
Hatchingtide is upon us once again! This year's is sure to be the most spectacular yet!
I wonder how many people will be able to solve Nonotta and Riggy's puzzle? I fear that not everyone in Eorzea is as clever as you,  !
At first I thought the egg hunt would be too difficult, but you made it look easy!
Riggy help gabby friend!
For patrons who prefer intellectual stimulation, we have mahjong. For everyone else, we have Cuff-a-Cur.
Tell me, do you believe in luck? When the final tile to a winning hand falls into place, is it divine providence that grants you victory, or your own foresight?
Time for a quick game? There are a few things I'm supposed to be doin', but they can wait.
Sorry, but I'm tryin' to remember all the things Utata sent me to get. Lost my list, see?
I can't wait to tell the other Redbills about beatin' the famous  . No need to mention it was only in a card game, is there?
Oh. That's not what I was expectin'... Maybe I should get some better cards?
Well, all things considered, I'd say that was a fair result. But I think I can spare the time for another hand, if you're game.
Would you care to indulge me in a game using these charming cards I found amidst the undergrowth?
I am dreadfully sorry, but Master Matoya has expressly forbidden me from partaking in such leisurely pursuits until my errands are done.
I say, that was rather enjoyable! This will be one to tell my tadpoles!
Oh dear. Perhaps the cognitive faculties that Master Matoya has bestowed upon me are insufficient in some manner...
Now that is a surprise! To think that a mere poroggo such as myself could stand on equal footing with someone so abundantly intelligent!
While I cannot permit any unauthorized persons beyond this point, our rules do not prohibit anyone from standing where you are now. Or from playing cards, for that matter...
Although I am partial to the occasional game of cards, I sense the presence of my ever-watchful superiors nearby. Perhaps another time.
I must say, I was expecting a little more competition. Nonetheless, I thank you for helping me pass the time.
Had I known you would prove such a formidable opponent, I would have played my best cards from the outset. Should you agree to another match, you will not find me such easy prey.
Now that the warm-up is over, perhaps we can both start playing seriously.
I'm sure these crates won't go anywhere while I have a game of cards. Just promise not to tell Master Garlond!
I would love to play cards, but Jessie told me to watch these crates like a hawk. Not to mention, I think she's watching me like one, too.
I can't believe it! I won! Wait a moment─are you sure you didn't lose on purpose?
Hmm... A slight miscalculation on my part. I'm probably just tired from looking at crates all nightmorningdaynight.
Interesting... Our individual strengths and weaknesses in perfect equilibrium. If we were to play again, would the outcome be the same? This warrants further testing.
A challenge, is it? Excellent─I was hoping to test a new strategy I've been working on before I play against my more experienced friend!
Please, no cards right now─I need to think. I shall let you know when I have conceived of a match-worthy tactic.
I won? I won! I can finally bring my deck to bear against Botan and─ Ah, but am I truly ready? Mayhap a few more victories under my belt first...
...Another defeat. It seems I must refine my strategies ere I can pose a credible threat to Botan...
Hm, I managed to battle you to an impasse. My skills have improved, but is it enough? I will hardly impress Botan with a stalemate...
The imperials have not gained any ground since our last battle, but neither have we. I fear this stalemate can only continue for so long.
Gods, nobody annoys me more than Whastrach. We were what you might call “friends” at one point, but even then, he always looked down on me.
This sickness which plagues Alphinaud and the others is unlike anything I have ever seen. To see them as they are and be powerless to help them... It is a pain beyond words.
Both Mistress Krile and Master Matoya have taken up the search for a cure to this strange sleeping sickness. I pray they find a remedy soon.
If you've come to ask after Y'shtola and the others, I'm afraid there's been no change. Rest assured we're doing everything we can to help them.
Welcome to the Hard Place!
Welcome! May I interest you in a bottle or three of our house spirit?
This costume is surprisingly comfortable, but the headpiece does begin to feel heavy after a while. How ever does Master Adkiragh manage to wear it all the time?
Greetings, MistressMaster  . I'm pleased to report that our Ishgardian cuisine has proven tremendously popular.
The chief suggested that we wear the same headpiece. We...politely declined.
The two brothers were once close, but at some point Bulugan began to drift away. And despite his boisterous demeanor, the chief can be given to bashfulness. So the distance between them remains.
To be a blue mage, you need to go and discover things for yourself! You'll be doin' a fair bit of walkin', too, so it might be worth investin' in a sturdier pair of boots at some point.
Let me tell you somethin',  . There are more important things in life than money. I once knew a man who forgot that, and─well, never you mind. Just remember what I said.
Hello, mate! How's the spellbook comin' along? Filled it up yet?
As for your performances, if you keep this up, you'll have nearly as many fans as me!
Latool Ja and Gaheel Ja know Martyn for many years. Guide him around New World, we did. Now we assistants. Pay not so good, sometimes dangerous, too. But we like Martyn anyway.
Some people think Latool Ja is Gaheel Ja and Gaheel Ja is Latool Ja! Ha! Silly Eorzeans!
Martyn love blue very much. Blue clothes, blue hair, blue underwear, blue assistants. Ah! Maybe that why he hire us!
Every day, Martyn fight in arena. He have so many bruises, his skin slowly turning blue.
Martyn must stay in infirmary. Martyn ask for blue bandages, but only have white. Silly Martyn! Always thinking “blue this, blue that”!
Ul'dah very interesting city! Even have cornmeal, like Mamool Ja recipe. So much cornmeal, Latool Ja need two heads to eat it all. But Latool Ja only have one head...

I first met Martyn when he came to live with us, along with Whastrach. While they were both committed to their research, they always helped around the village however they could. <sigh> It all seems so long ago now.
Martyn has hardly changed at all since then, but Whastrach... It saddens me deeply to think of what he has become. Please, you must make him see sense!
You did it! Whastrach was more powerful than I could've imagined, but you beat him!
I do hope your Little Ladies' Day dreams are coming true, my ladylord! If not, I have a few things that should help─or rather, I will have them shortly, so please come back in a bit.
Valentione's Day is upon us once more, and I, Lisette de Valentione, have come to fill hearts the realm over with the warmth of love, passionate and pure!
Our events will capture your heart, too, adventurer! Or, at least they will once you've done me the tiniest of favors...
Would you mind checking in on little Astrid for me? She's still quite new to all this, and I'd feel sooo much better if someone lent her delicate efforts a steadying hand.
How are you enjoying the festivities? Have your fortune told! Your affinity divined! Let us all celebrate this wondrous day of love together!
Thanks to your timely aid, our celebrations have reached new heights of song-worthy passion!
And yet I cannot help but worry that those less pure of heart turn these giddy festivities to their own unsavory purposes...
You have discharged your duties, my champion of love! Go now, and enjoy the celebrations with a heart full of frolicsome fun.
Lisette eagerly awaits those who would know their fortunes! Or if you would undertake the ceremony once more, a House Valentione servant stands ready to conduct you to the venue!
Taggy has embraced the spirit of the celebrations with more enthusiasm than I expected...but it does bring me joy to see her so joyous.
Did Lisie tell you!? Our next attempt at the ceremony was smooth as Ul'dahn silk! In fact, it was such a lark, I think we might go through again!
Gimme a miracle elixir!
Hatchingtide is underway! If you'd like to take part, speak with Jihli Aliapoh, the festival founder!
Have you done your part for the Valentione's Day celebrations? Once you've assisted Lady Astrid, I should be happy to give a free reading on romance for you and a partner of your choice.
Heading out on an adventure? Forget the weather─you need a forecast on treasure! Assist the Valentiones with their festivities, and I shall share with you the fate of your material fortune.
As part of the Valentione's Day festivities, I can offer you an affinity reading of indisputable accuracy. Come stand before me once you have discharged your duty to ardor and affection.
Valentione's Day is upon us once more, and I, Lisette de Valentione, have come to fill hearts the realm over with the warmth of love, passionate and pure!
How stands the reservoir of rapture within your bosom, adventurer? Whomever your favored partner might be, our fortune-tellers can help sound the depths of your unplumbed affinity!
The mechanical soldiers of rumor─some people say they're a new type of imperial weaponry. Well, there's only one way to confirm this: we take one apart! For science!
Under the auspices of the Gold Saucer, Garlond Ironworks will soon be offering guests a selection of special prizes. Do not miss this rare opportunity!
I don't know why this time should be any different. <sigh> I'm such a failure...
In order to undertake this quest, you must first complete one of the following main scenario quests: “The Gridanian Envoy,” “The Ul'dahn Envoy,” or “The Lominsan Envoy.”

Do you love MGP? Then you best get yourself over to the Gold Saucer and make the most of the fifty percent bonus rewards on offer during this season's limited-time event! Did I mention it's only for a limited time!?
Latool Ja cannot wait to see Azulmagia lose! Send him and silly costume to seventh hell!
beat Azulmagia! But now Latool Ja must give Gaheel Ja ten gil... Why, say  ? Ha ha! No reason...

The other day, a man from the East Aldenard Trading Company paid us a visit. He said that they needed hands for the rebuilding effort in Gyr Abania. That they were looking to hire folk among the poor and the displaced.

Long have I cursed my lot and the powers that be. I thought that I would die with a curse on my lips. To suddenly be given another chance... Can this be true? Can there really be a better life for us?
Do you not feel it in the air, adventurer? 'Tis Valentione's Day, and love, uh...runs rampant through the streets!
We of House Valentione have returned to spread our message of Ardor and Affection, and honor the pure pursuits of our ancestor, Countess Arabelle.
In order to undertake the quest “A Many-splendored Thing,” you must first complete the quest “It's Probably Pirates.”
The Garlond Ironworks, the researchers at Saint Coinach's Find─everyone is pitching in to help find that beacon. It won't be long now. Just you wait.
Hmm, how very odd. You, I mean. Your appearance, rather...
Seeing as we've set up a site here anyway, we decided to conduct a thorough investigation of the tower's base.
You have been warned, mortal. Bear this in mind should you choose to stay your course.
(I'll stop calling Sid a chocobo's arse when he stops thinking of me as a stupid little girl. Gods, you'd think after everything we've been through he'd give me a little more credit...)
(It's because I'm so bloody short. I'm due for a growth spurt, but I don't know if I'll ever be as tall as he is...)
Hmm... Something about you seems so very... No, it can't be. As if I could have possibly seen my future business partner in a dream. What a preposterous thing that would be...

Honesty above all─such is the principle that informs our every decision here at the Boutique of Splendors. I am a fervent believer in the idea that a frank and open business relationship will benefit all parties.
It's a bit odd how this new training ground of ours is being utilized mostly by foreign fighters. Four out of five we ferry to the isle aren't Kholusian. But hey, at least it's not going to waste...?
From here, our journey continues. The journey to revive the Fist of Rhalgr.
Pray watch over us, Adri...
Right, let's go and pound those soldiers into shape!
I must keep an eye on Zentsa lest she...enjoy teaching a little too much.
? If you are still worried for me, you need not be. I will be fine...though I am glad you came to visit.
We were just discussing where we should try training next! Did you want to come...?
We're being very hardworking and well behaved, I promise! After all, if we don't train properly, we'll never be as good as you!
You want to make use of this practice ground? Well, you'd best ask permission from the Eulmorans first─they were the ones who put the place back in order.
! What brings you to the Rookery? Come to prepare more Berube cuisine, perhaps?
, always good to see you. Let's have another bout soon, eh? I'll make sure I'm ready for you next time.
I've danced in deserts beneath the burning sun, in lush forests, atop snow-swept peaks... I can't wait to see where my journey will take me next!
I have relied on your kindness and talent for far too long already. And so I intend to scout out new dancers who can help shoulder the burden. Perhaps Lhaminn could introduce me to someone...?
No, no, no... None of these milksops'll do...
I feel so...normal. I can hardly believe it!
I can walk through town without being pursued by bounty hunters. I can meet with Alka in broad daylight─er, for training, of course! But maybe someday...
Ah,  . I can only apologize once more for the role I played in the recent...farce to which you were forced to be party. Rest assured that there will be no more of that.
As for Lady Leveva─she seems satisfied with the pace of her progress at the moment. She was practically skipping with joy last we spoke, in fact.
Greetings,  ! Your wondrous adventures are keeping you occupied, I trust? I find myself with relatively few demands on my time.
Joye has all but taken the reins when it comes to instructing our machinists, leaving me free to concentrate on running the manufactory.
Yes, I am proud indeed to see my protégés seize their independence...if not a little sad that they have left the nest.
If you've come to see how we're doin', then I'm happy to report that me and the Hounds are havin' a grand old time sniffin' about Ishgard.
One thing still bothers me though: do you know how Joye does that thing with her hair? You know, when she pulls out her firearm? I'm startin' to think I'll never get an answer...

The sin eater Phronesis, one of those damnable Virtues, wanders the wastelands, wreaking havoc on all who pass with his baleful magicks. If only there were a mage of sufficient skill willing to lend ol' Cerigg a helping hand.
Don't you worry, now. Ol' Cerigg will pay you your share of the bounty from his own coinpurse.
For a boy his age, Taynor's got a good head on his shoulders. Why, he's already tightened our finances considerably─mostly by cutting back on my liquor budget.

Each day, I endeavor to repay my debt to Cerigg as best I can. Preparing our meals, managing our funds, studying my magic... He tells me I work too hard, but─as I always tell him─I have a hundred years of my life to make up for!
Triple Triad? Why yes, I certainly am partial to a game between pouring drinks.
As it's all the rage amongst our customers, it would be remiss of me not to learn how to play it myself.
I'm afraid now is not the best of times, though. I've a feeling we're about to get busy.
It seems fortune was on my side this time, but I daresay you might come out on top were we to play again.
Hmm... Even though I lost, you've taught me a valuable lesson. My next opponent had best be careful!
Interesting... Despite ending in a stalemate, that was rather an exhilarating game. Care for another?
Say, aren't you Feo Ul's sapling? When they still lived in Lydha Lran, we used to have lots of fun together, making mischief on travelers.
Ooh, ooh! Do you know these pretty cards with pictures on them? Urianger gave some to me way back when, saying that they're for a mortal game. If you have the same cards, let's play, let's play!
I'm sorry, but I can't play with you right now. I'm busy thinking up a fiendish new prank─I-I mean...a fun new game!
I won, I won! Tee hee, such a fine feeling it is to beat a mortal at herhis own mortal game!
Nooo, how can this be? How can a pixie be bested at play? We must play again! Yes, again and again until I win!
Pffft, what a boring way to end! We must play again! Yes, again and again until I win!
Triple Triad? Why, yes, my brother taught me. I know the rules well enough if you wish to play.
My brother loved to play Triple Triad, but he left his cards with me when he went to the Crystarium. He feared it might distract from his training.
I thought it a waste to let his cards gather dust so I've practiced when time allows.
Goodness, I won. I'll have to thank my brother for his lessons.
I was so certain I had you. Perhaps with a little more practice...
I certainly wasn't expecting a draw, though I suppose it was bound to happen eventually. Would you care to try and break the tie?
I sort of inherited these cards, you see. I'm sure my friend would be happy to see them put to good use, wherever she is.
These cards were inside that chest my friend left behind. For playing Triple Triad, they are. You've heard of it, haven't you?
Thought so. Well, if you ever fancy a game or two, you know where to find me. After all, you're the one who solved her riddle. Maybe you can win some of her old cards, too?
Ha ha! I knew she had good taste when it came to Triple Triad cards.
Hmm... Even with a deck like this, I still lost. I guess there's more to it than having decent cards.
A draw, eh? Seems a fair result, but my friend was never one to leave things unfinished, and neither am I. What do you say to another game?
Look! I got amazing cards from a big, happy lady. Oh, do you have some, too!? We should play!
You want to play now...? I might not be a grown-up, but I still have things to do. Sorry.
Yes! ...You didn't let me win, did you?
I guess that's what I get for playing against a grown-up...
A draw? Well, that's boring. You need to have a winner and a loser!

Isn't Captain Lyna just the best? She was the reason I joined the guard, you know. I've always wanted to tell her that. And yet, I'll be damned if I don't get all nervous and clam up every time she walks in the room.
The other day, Thancred taught me this card game, saying it'd be the perfect way to break the ice. But I just can't seem to figure out the rules. Any chance you could teach me?
I'd love to chat more, but it's almost time for our drills, and I've already skipped them twice this week.
What's that you say? I won!? I'm not sure how that happened, but I'll take it nonetheless! If I tell Captain Lyna I beat you, do you think she'll be impressed?
I lost? Well, that's a shame. I'll never have the courage to talk to Captain Lyna at this rate...
I think I'm actually starting to get the hang of this! A few more games, and I daresay I might just be able to work up the courage to approach Captain Lyna!

Teetsh aren't my shole passhion, I'll have you know. Lately I've taken to collecting more of shese cardsh I picked up when I lasht went ashore. I'm told they can be used to play a game? Will you teach me?

Hmm? Cardsh? No, no, I've no time for that right now. I'm bushy taking shtock of my precioush teetsh collection─which is shtill short a shet of finlessh ones, by the way. Are you sure you can't spare a few? No? Hmph.
What? I won!? Hahaha! Thish is almost as fun as pulling teetsh! Not quite, but almosht! Let ush play again!
So I losht huh? Shtill, I feel as though I am beginning to grashp the bashic shtrategies. Next time, victory will be mine!
Shomehow this draw is more disshatisfying than a loss. Perhapsh it is the lack of resolution? I say, we should play again! For teetsh, this time!
Normally, I'm rather disinclined to speak with those who would interrupt my wine-tasting sessions.
For Triple Triad, I'm willing to make an exception.
The resident performers are somewhat more deserving of my attention at this precise moment. Move along, please.
Well, that was to be expected. You could have at least tried to make it interesting for me, though.
Every dog has its day, and perhaps this was yours? Enjoy it while it lasts.
A draw? It seems another game is required to put you in your place.
There are some within the Order who were less than pleased with Sister Lalai's reinstatement. But Prioress Dewlala has spoken, and none would dare to question her judgment.
Will she be truly accepted by her peers? That depends on how she conducts herself from here on. Let it suffice to say that I, for one, will be watching her very closely.

Eorzea survived the Calamity and has effected a miraculous rebirth. 'Tis for all who struggle onwards, putting one foot in front of the other as they travel this unfamiliar and oft-uneven path, that I dedicate this song of safe passage...
Adventurer! I must thank you again for helping me delve into the details of this story. You will see─and hopefully read─the full article in The Raven forthwith!
, it's good to see you! Alpha was here for a visit, too, no so long ago, on the heels of that bossy little Omega.
It came in demanding we improve its climate shielding, so I took care of it myself. Now they're headed back to Garlemald to “test the efficacy” of my work. Cheeky bugger.

After that, they planned on revisiting Sharlayan, then striking out to new destinations in Eorzea and the Far East. Sounds like they'll be in need of a good scrub once they get back, the pair of them.
Aye, I still stop in for a drink now and then. Checking up on me, sinner? That's kind of you.
My work takes me all over, much like yours does, I wager. But whenever I find myself near Wright, I make sure to visit Milinda's grave.
It doesn't...I wouldn't say it hurts like it used to. I've made my peace with it, best I can. But she'll always be a part of me. The better part, probably.
What awaits when one passes beyond mortality's veil, I cannot say. Nevertheless, I would like to believe that in death, Branden and Lady Sauldia have found the happiness that eluded them in life.
I'll keep living the way my loved ones would have wanted me to...and do my best to bring a little light into the lives of others.
I regret to inform you that we are not looking for new suppliers for the time being. However, should there be a change of circumstances, we may have reason to call on your services.
If you are capable of fulfilling any of our orders, you will receive scrips for your efforts.
Unfortunately, the Boutique of Splendors has suspended all scrip exchanges until further notice.
We have a wide range of wares available, should you possess the necessary scrips.

Esoteric volumes, you say? We at the Boutique can only allow our most distinguished of customers to peruse such wares, lest they be devalued by falling into the hands of any passing cobbler or kettlesmith.
※ You must complete a quest offered by Guiding Star in Revenant's Toll in order to purchase master recipes.
Sorry, sinner, but my services are reserved for members of Clan Nutsy.
※ In order to be eligible for the quest “Nuts to You,” you must have met the following requirements:

※ You must have completed the sidequest “Elite and Dangerous.”
※ You must have completed the main scenario quest “Travelers of Norvrandt.”
You and me've got no business, friend. Nutters only. Go and see Halldor in the Crystarium if that's not to your liking.
※ In order to be eligible for the quest “Nuts to You,” you must have met the following requirements:

※ You must have completed the sidequest “Elite and Dangerous.”
※ You must have completed the main scenario quest “Travelers of Norvrandt.”
You were a big help,  , but I think between the four of us, we can keep the Bellows running without resorting to a diet of worms. ...Probably.
Don't you worry: no matter what problems show up, my trusty hammer and I will be here to beat them down!
Fear not for the Iron Bellows! I, Sue-Rend, will endeavor to educate Colana and Iola in the lost art of common sense!
Hurielle is showing definite signs of improvement. We have you, Frithrik, and Lobb to thank for that.

The three of you showed me what an important role the facet plays in keeping the citizenry in good health, and I'll be sure to teach the younger members to think beyond simply reeling in as many fish as possible.
Welcome! We've assembled a veritable host of exclusive seasonal goods for any and all adventurers who are willing to lend us a hand in cleaning up the beach.
...But I'm afraid we're not open for business quite yet. Pray come back after the Rising festivities have commenced in earnest.
I'm sorry, but we're right in the midst of our preparations. Could you come back another time?
You're an inspiration,  ─an ideal I'll surpass one day yet!
Well met, khagan! Our training is as intense as ever, but we'd welcome another axe. Care to join the fray?
Welcome to your home away from home, the Wandering Stairs, where we serve the finest ale you'll find this side of the Crystarium. Courtesy of the Facet of Nourishing, of course.
Ah,  ! I'm pleased to say my sessions of the Legend of Musosai are as popular as ever. A toast to the old man, who helps make me rich even in death!
But what of yourself, my friend? Embarked on any exciting adventures of late? Remember, if you have any new tales to share, I'm all ears!
Beggin' your pardon, but aren't you the samurai who was with Master Musosai? You and him saved me─from that vile moneylender. Thanks to you, I could go back to nurse Da back to health.
When I heard that Master Musosai had passed away, I came to pay my respects. May Thal rest his soul...
Y-You! You may not remember me, but my name is Honfraint. We met but briefly when you found me despairing of life under my ruthless father.

After that day, I left Ishgard behind and took to wandering the realm. Soon after arriving in Ul'dah, I learned Master Musosai had passed away. Though I did not learn his name until later, his words saved me; the least I can do is to offer my prayers in return.
Our work here is done! One fewer evil afflicts the realm!
Master Musosai's great and all, but I'm rather partial to his pupil. Ah, I'd love to meet herhim one day...
Welcome to the Silver Bazaar! Might I interest you in our specialty, Musosai Dumplings? Or perhaps a set of authentic samurai attire, imported directly from the Far East.
...You don't have a clue, do you? Take yourself to the Quicksand and listen to the tale─the Legend of Musosai. We'll see if you aren't clamoring for my wares then!
Although not everyone here is an adventurer, you'd have to be quite adventurous to even come here in the first place!
I heard that stonetomes contain a wealth of ancient knowledge, which is what makes them so valuable. But how did they get the information into those tiny things? And how do we get it out again?
I often join expeditions to hunt for stonetomes, whereas Radovan only occasionally comes along. He says, “Once in a while is fine, but I don't want it to turn into a daily grind.” Hmph!
When they lay, you can bet that I'll be the first at those eggs. Oh, yes. No more goin' hungry on the days that they don't come to give us meol, not for me!
Vauthry... Eeeeeeggs...
These are roosters! Some elven boy came by and told me. Can you believe that no one else bothered to say nothin'? Not in the whole time I was sitting here, waitin' for them to lay eggs!
No, I won't “just eat them, already”! Sure, they're useless, what with not being able to lay eggs and all, but we're friends now!
Don't worry yourself, sinner─it's just a bit of sport between friends. And gleeful onlookers, I suppose.
That's some appetite for violence they've got, I'll admit. But I'm sure you understand the need to work off stress somehow─and there's plenty of that to go around down here, Vauthry or no.
“The sight of the night sky really gets the blood pumping,” they said. I'm beginning to suspect that they just enjoy having the pulp beaten out of them...
Come inside, see my dance! It's an experience you won't soon forget! Free of charge─just make sure you tell all of your free citizen friends!
Lord Vauthry! Let me dance for you!
You, there! Have you any food? The meol's stopped coming, and I can't dance on an empty stomach...
You─have you need of a personal entertainer? Or even a simple guide? Please, I'll do anything...
I came here looking for my─er, friend of mine. Bit of a shite town, innit?
I see you're not babbling about that “Vauthry” fellow. Not sure what's come over everyone else, but it's right creepy, if you ask me.
Never did find the one I came here to see. It seems he found himself a patron, and then...gone. Just like that. I─ It's a shame. He was a good man.
Hee hee! What is it, hm? Can't you let this old rat sit in peace?
Now we know why the missing left no corpses, eh? The rats down here, we never questioned what we were eating...
The dark of night is no comfort to an aging rat like me. I see their faces looking down at me─old friends who died such brutal deaths in the war against the eaters...
Lots of discarded objects end up here─some valuable. I figure that if I work the gold from them into something nice, at least one of those Eulmorans will recognize my talents.
With Vauthry gone, there's next to no chance of any of us living the high life up in Eulmore. Most folks have given up on finding ways to show off their skills...
I haven't─not entirely. But it helps that I can find clams out here, along with the gold for smithing. A man has to eat, you know?
The night returning is all well and good, but for the moment, it only means less time when I can actually see what I'm turning up...
Seeing these huge ships split like so much firewood really makes you think, doesn't it? The Flood must have been awe-inspiring, in its own terrible way.
We're free, sure. But where do we go from here? Where is there to go?
I know not what's out there, but now that there's a sea to sail, I intend to find out. There must be plans somewhere, designs for building new ships...
Hm? Oh, if you need directions, I'm afraid I'm not the best person to ask. I've but recently come here myself from the Crystarium. Thought I'd see what all of the fuss is about.
So far I haven't been able to get in to see the so-called gilded paradise of Eulmore, but it's fine. I can be very stubborn when the situation calls for it...
What's the matter with everyone? I feel like I've missed something...
Interesting to see Vauthry deposed, but if you ask me, he was only a symptom. The citizens, and even those out here knocking at the gates... Man's avarice is the true disease, isn't it?
I have a feeling that there's not much left to see here. I might return to the Crystarium soon─that's where the world will begin again, mark my words.
Most of the wood and iron you see around the Derelicts was scavenged from those old sunken ships. Not the finest of materials, but we've managed well enough so far.
Not that I'm particularly missing the taste of meol, but not having it does mean less food to go around overall, and it's hard to build on an empty stomach...
It's happening! I've found a bunch of people who are interested in rebuilding the ships! We're going to take everything that can be spared and build something seaworthy─just you watch.
You've been permitted entry? Hmph. Well, just be sure you go directly to the Bureau of Immigration once inside.
Lord Vauthry! All hail!
I have been apprised of the full details by the young woman in your party. Your intervention did free us all, so I suppose I shan't detain you for entering the city under false pretenses. This time.
Yes, yes, the gate is now open to all. Just don't make a fuss.
You hangin' around here for the free meol? Don't touch the stuff, meself. Tastes like rot and socks. Rottin' socks, even.
What in the blindin' hells is going on?
I knew there was somethin' fishy about that meol. But preyin' on the starvin' and desperate like that...that's just dirty.
All that's left here are the dyin' and the downtrodden. Someone's got to help 'em if we're to put this world right.
If you're here to speak with Hathenbet, mind your manners. I realize he looks...like that, but he's an honorable man, and I won't see him disrespected.
